line_1: Their praise has been by fame proclaim'd,
line_2: My brethren all for valour fam'd,

line_1: Since by thy Saviour's voice it is proclaim'd,
line_2: That wheresoe'er his gospel shall be nam'd,
When they heard their leader named.

line_1: But, soon as Fame the fairy-gifts proclaim'd,
line_2: Quick-rising wrath his ready soul inflamed

line_1: Nor wonder at her charms proclaimed; ....
line_2: At her no telescopes were aimed,
